{"body":"## Context\n\n`claude-code-telegrammer` currently includes YAML-based agent orchestration commands (`claude-code-telegrammer start config/telegram-master.yaml`) that belong in `scitex-agent-container`.\n\nAs part of a Separation of Concerns refactoring, these are being removed from `claude-code-telegrammer`.\n\n## Scope\n\n**claude-code-telegrammer** (done/in-progress):\n- Dropping `claude-code-telegrammer start <yaml>` command\n- Dropping `config/telegram-master.yaml` as a user-facing feature\n- Focusing on: MCP server + watchdog components only\n- Launch command: `claude --dangerously-load-development-channels server:claude-code-telegrammer`\n\n**scitex-agent-container** (TODO):\n- Should own the YAML-based agent lifecycle (`start/stop/status/attach`)\n- Should consume `claude-code-telegrammer` as a pip dependency for MCP + watchdog\n- Should manage: screen sessions, `.mcp.json` generation, the `--dangerously-load-development-channels` flag\n- Reference config: `claude-code-telegrammer/config/telegram-master.yaml`\n\n**scitex-orochi** (TODO):\n- Verify MCP server name changed from `\"telegram\"` to `\"claude-code-telegrammer\"`\n- Update any references to `server:telegram` → `server:claude-code-telegrammer`\n- Update any `.mcp.json` templates that reference the old name\n\n## Affected repos\n- `claude-code-telegrammer`\n- `scitex-agent-container`\n- `scitex-orochi`","labels":[],"title":"SoC: Move YAML-based agent orchestration from claude-code-telegrammer to scitex-agent-container","url":"https://github.com/ywatanabe1989/todo/issues/172"}

