commit 624a63da4b70c30f0be597c6da63abfa2bcd806d
Author: Yusuke Watanabe <ywatanabe@scitex.ai>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 10:03:49 2026 +0900

    refactor: remove all Orochi-specific code (SoC)
    
    scitex-agent-container is now a generic agent lifecycle library with
    zero Orochi knowledge. All Orochi-specific plumbing has been moved into
    scitex-orochi (see scitex_orochi._agent_container_bridge), which now
    preprocesses the yaml, generates the MCP config file, resolves the
    workspace token, injects the relevant claude flags, and starts the
    sidecar thread itself — calling agent_start with a shim yaml.
    
    Removed:
      - src/scitex_agent_container/runtimes/orochi_mcp.py (182 lines)
      - src/scitex_agent_container/orochi_connector.py (189 lines)
      - tests/test_orochi_connector.py (301 lines)
      - config/templates/test-orochi.yaml
      - OrochiSpec dataclass + the ``orochi`` field on AgentConfig
      - YAML parser for ``spec.orochi:`` (the section is now silently
        ignored by agent-container; scitex-orochi parses it itself)
      - Orochi import + start_orochi_sidecar() call from lifecycle.py
      - Orochi import + get_orochi_claude_flags() call from claude_code.py
      - config.orochi.is_enabled checks in _needs_auto_accept and
        _send_auto_accept_keystrokes — these now key on the actual flag
        list, so any caller that injects --dangerously-load-development-
        channels gets the right auto-accept behavior automatically
    
    Also in this commit:
      - cli.py 687 lines → 24-line shim, with logic split into cli_pkg/
        (8 files, all <200 lines, no behavior change). This was needed to
        add stop --all / stop --force / start --force without hitting the
        project's 512-line file limit.
      - New library functions:
        - agent_stop(name, force=True) — tolerate stale registry / hooks
        - agent_stop_all(force=True) — bulk stop every registered agent
        - agent_start(..., force=True) — pre-stop existing then start
      - resolve_config() default user_dir changed from
        ~/.scitex/orochi/agents/ to ~/.scitex/agent-container/agents/
        (orochi was a leak in the path itself)
    
    scitex-orochi v0.6.x or later is now required for the launch flow to
    work. Direct callers of scitex-agent-container that previously relied
    on the Orochi auto-config will need to either install scitex-orochi
    and use ``scitex-orochi launch`` instead, or generate their own MCP
    config + sidecar.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

