commit 0580d98b9a3237bc4c8eda2a832e5daf3c146e4f
Author: Yusuke Watanabe <ywatanabe@scitex.ai>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 10:04:45 2026 +0900

    feat: own Orochi plumbing as agent-container dispatcher (SoC)
    
    Pairs with the scitex-agent-container refactor that removed all
    Orochi-specific code from that package. scitex-orochi is now the
    "Orochi dispatcher" — it consumes scitex-agent-container as a
    generic lifecycle library and owns every Orochi-specific concern
    itself.
    
    New subpackage: scitex_orochi._agent_container_bridge
      - spec.py: OrochiSpec dataclass + load_orochi_spec(yaml_path)
        (moved from scitex_agent_container.config.OrochiSpec)
      - mcp.py: build_orochi_mcp_config / write_mcp_config_file
        (moved from scitex_agent_container.runtimes.orochi_mcp)
      - connector.py: start_orochi_sidecar / resolve_orochi_token
        (moved from scitex_agent_container.orochi_connector)
      - All three modules adapted to take OrochiSpec / agent_name /
        labels / env as explicit args instead of pulling them off
        AgentConfig.orochi (which no longer exists).
      - resolve_orochi_token() now has a bash -l fallback so callers
        whose non-interactive shell hasn't sourced the secrets file
        can still get the workspace token (the "telegrammer spawning
        a head" case).
    
    scitex_orochi._cli.commands._launch_helpers
      - launch_via_agent_container() is now the dispatcher:
          1. Loads spec.orochi from the raw yaml
          2. Generates the MCP config file (with token resolution)
          3. Builds a shim yaml in /tmp with --mcp-config and
             --dangerously-load-development-channels injected into
             claude.flags (deduped against any pre-existing flags)
          4. Calls scitex_agent_container.lifecycle.agent_start on
             the shim yaml — agent-container has no idea anything
             Orochi is going on
          5. After agent_start returns, starts the Orochi sidecar
             thread in this process so the agent registers with the
             hub
      - Added _prepare_orochi_shim_yaml() helper
      - Added --force flag to all three launch subcommands
        (master / head / all) — passes through to agent_start
    
    New command: scitex-orochi stop
      - new file: _cli/commands/stop_cmd.py
      - "scitex-orochi stop NAME" — stop one fleet agent
      - "scitex-orochi stop --all" — stop every fleet agent (telegrammer
        auto-skipped, same as launch all)
      - "--force" passes through to agent_stop, tolerating stale
        registry / hooks / missing configs
    
    This completes the SoC refactor: scitex-agent-container is a generic
    agent lifecycle library, scitex-orochi is its Orochi-aware dispatcher.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

